cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.SY

This paper deals with the coexistence of RF and VLC communications in indoor environments, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the concept of effective capacity, which is a measure of the maximum constant arrival data rate at the transmitter buffer when QoS needs are imposed as limits on the buffer overflow and delay violation probabilities. This concept is related to information theory and capacity analysis, which are covered in cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the effects of illumination needs and line-of-sight blockage on the VLC performance, which are related to multimedia systems and applications, covered in cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also considers the impact of different physical aspects and data-link QoS needs on the effective capacity and delay bounds, which are related to security and cryptography, covered in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and control systems, covered in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
